@realmoney Mar 25, 2019 | 09:13 AM EDT DOUG KASS How Will the Release of Attorney General Barr's Summary of the Mueller Report Impact the Markets? * It's a nothing burger! Most of the investors I spoke to expected the markets to have a "relief rally" - particularly after

Friday's market schmeissing. This, at least for the moment, has not happened - indeed, overnight futures were down fairly hard (but have since rallied back to break even). Many Republicans who are pro-Trump will likely view the delivery of the Mueller Report and the Barr

summary as exoneration of the president. While many Democrats will see this weekend's Barr summary as written by a partisan who already (in a widely circulated memorandum last year) was critical of the Mueller investigation. Regardless of one's political views my quick answer

is that the release of the Bar letter will have virtually no impact on the markets. * The conclusion, in the main, was in line with the consensus expectation. Speaker Pelosi seemed to have telegraphed this a week or two ago when she stated impeachment should not be an option.

Nor will this weekend's output likely have much impact on voters' views - especially important as we move into the 2020 election. We must remember that the Mueller investigation likely had very little impact on the Democratic party's 2018 mid-term election victory -
as the primary issues were healthcare and jobs. This weekend's news was a nothing burger for the markets. @jimcramer @tomkeene @cnbcfastmoney @SquawkCNBC @TeamCavuto
